<div1 type="poem" id="d3">
<head>
Hymn of Breaking Strain.
</head>
<pb n="382" id="KipBrea382"/>
<lg type="stanza">
<l>The careful text books measure</l>
<l>  (Let all who build beware!)</l>
<l>The load, the shock, the pressure</l>
<l>  Material can bear.</l>
<l>So, when the buckled girder</l>
<l>  Lets down the grinding span,</l>
<l>The blame of loss, or murder,</l>
<l>  Is laid upon the man.</l>
<l><hi rend="italic">     Not on the Stuff &mdash; the Man!</hi></l>
</lg><lg type="stanza">
<l>But in our daily dealing</l>
<l>  With stone and steel, we find</l>
<l>The Gods have no such feeling</l>
<l>  Of justice toward mankind.</l>
<l>To no set gauge they make us, &mdash; </l>
<l>  For no laid course prepare &mdash; </l>
<l>And presently o'ertake us</l>
<l>  With loads we cannot bear.</l>
<l><hi rend="italic">   Too merciless to bear.</hi></l>
</lg><lg type="stanza">
<l>The prudent text-books give it</l>
<l>  In tables at the end &mdash; </l>
<l>The stress that shears a rivet</l>
<l>  Or makes a tie-bar bend &mdash; </l>
<l>What traffic wrecks macadam &mdash; </l>
<l>  What concrete should endure &mdash; </l>
<l>But we, poor Sons of Adam,</l>
<l>  Have no such literature,</l>
<l><hi rend="italic">   To warn us or make sure!</hi></l>
</lg><lg type="stanza">
<l>We hold all Earth to plunder &mdash; </l>
<l>  All Time and Space as well &mdash; </l>
<l>Too wonder-stale to wonder</l>
<l>  At each new miracle;</l>
<pb n="383" id="KipBrea383"/>
<l>Till, in mid-illusion</l>
<l>  Of Godhead 'neath our hand,</l>
<l>Falls multiple confusion</l>
<l>  On all we did or planned.</l>
<l><hi rend="italic">    The mighty works we planned.</hi></l>
</lg><lg type="stanza">
<l>We only of Creation</l>
<l><hi rend="italic">(Oh, luckier bridge and rail!)</hi></l>
<l>Abide the twin-damnation &mdash; </l>
<l>  To fail and know we fail.</l>
<l>Yet we &mdash; by which sole token</l>
<l>  We know we once were Gods &mdash; </l>
<l>Take shame in being broken</l>
<l>  However great the odds &mdash; </l>
<l><hi rend="italic">   The Burden or the Odds.</hi></l>
</lg><lg type="stanza">
<l>Oh, veiled and secret Power</l>
<l>  Whose paths we seek in vain,</l>
<l>Be with us in our hour</l>
<l>  Of overthrow and pain;</l>
<l>That we &mdash; by which sure token</l>
<l>  We know thy ways are true &mdash; </l>
<l>In spite of being broken,</l>
<l><hi rend="italic">Because of being broken</hi>,</l>
<l><hi rend="italic">      May rise and build anew.</hi></l>
<l><hi rend="italic">      Stand up and build anew!</hi></l>
</lg>

</div1>
